{"60001":{"id":60001,"short_name":"Ibn al-Jawzi","full_name":"Ibn al-Jawzi","arabic":"","rank":7,"birth_date":"","birth_place":"","death_date":"597 AH","death_place":"","death_cause":"Natural","city":"","father_name":"","mother_name":"","interests":"4,5,6","bio":"A famous jurist, exegete, critic, preacher and a prolific author, with works on all subjects. He began his preaching career at a very young age and gained popularity amongst the masses. Although, he never met Ibn ‘Aqil, he did receive a fair amount of tutelage from his books, which left him perplexed about the orthodox doctrine of the Hanbali school; as reflected in his theological opinions that are often contradictory, and at times leaning towards allegorical exegesis (ta’wil) conflicting with the mainstream Hanbali position. His works in theology, thereafter, were criticised by the mainstream theologians of the Madhab, such as Ibn Qudama.","children":"","siblings":"","spouses":"","teachers":"","students":"","kunya":""},"60002":{"id":60002,"short_name":"‘Abdul-Qadir al-Jailani","full_name":"‘Abdul-Qadir al-Jailani","arabic":"","rank":7,"birth_date":"","birth_place":"","death_date":"561 AH","death_place":"","death_cause":"Natural","city":"","father_name":"","mother_name":"","interests":"4,5,6","bio":"A Hanbali theologian, great preacher and, perhaps the most influential Sufi figure who founded the Qadiriyah way (Tariqa). Although, his life is regarded as a chain of miracles, so much has been claimed about his ‘sainthood’ by his passionate Sufi followers that very little of his biographical accounts can be verified. The only book one can attribute to al-Jailani with a level of surety is al-Ghunya, in which he spells out his strict adherence to the Hanbali dogma and Law.","children":"","siblings":"","spouses":"","teachers":"","students":"","kunya":""},"60003":{"id":60003,"short_name":"Abu al-Khattab","full_name":"Abu al-Khattab","arabic":"","rank":7,"birth_date":"","birth_place":"","death_date":"510 AH","death_place":"","death_cause":"Natural","city":"","father_name":"","mother_name":"","interests":"4,5,6","bio":"A devout student of al-Qadhi Abu Ya’la, and author of many works in the Madhab, the most important of them: al-Intisar authored as a defence to various Hanbali juristic opinions in comparison to other schools. His students included many prominent Hanbali figures, such as ‘Abd al-Qadir al-Jailani.","children":"","siblings":"","spouses":"","teachers":"","students":"","kunya":""},"60010":{"id":60010,"short_name":"Ibn Mahmud Ibnul-Hasan","full_name":"Shaykh Abul-Fath Muhammad Ibn Mahmud Ibnul-Hasan al-Qazwini","arabic":"","rank":7,"birth_date":"","birth_place":"","death_date":"501 AH","death_place":"","death_cause":"Natural","city":"","father_name":"","mother_name":"","interests":"1,3,5","bio":"","children":"","siblings":"","spouses":"","teachers":"","students":"","kunya":""},"60011":{"id":60011,"short_name":"Ibn Muhammad (Ar-Rajib","full_name":"al-Lughawi Abul-Qasim al-Husayn Ibn Muhammad (Ar-Rajib al-Asfahani)","arabic":"","rank":7,"birth_date":"","birth_place":"","death_date":"502 AH","death_place":"","death_cause":"Natural","city":"","father_name":"","mother_name":"","interests":"1,3,5","bio":"","children":"","siblings":"","spouses":"","teachers":"","students":"","kunya":""},"60012":{"id":60012,"short_name":"Qinan Ibn Hamid al-Anbari","full_name":"Shaykh Abul-Fadl Muhammad Ibn Qinan Ibn Hamid al-Anbari","arabic":"","rank":7,"birth_date":"","birth_place":"","death_date":"503 AH","death_place":"","death_cause":"Natural","city":"","father_name":"","mother_name":"","interests":"1,3,5","bio":"","children":"","siblings":"","spouses":"","teachers":"","students":"","kunya":""},"60013":{"id":60013,"short_name":"Ibn Ahmad At-Tusi al-Ghazzali","full_name":"Imam Hujjatul-Islam Abu Hamid Muhammad Ibn Muhammad Ibn Ahmad At-Tusi al-Ghazzali","arabic":"","rank":7,"birth_date":"","birth_place":"","death_date":"505 AH","death_place":"","death_cause":"Natural","city":"","father_n